con (chat bubble + number) alongside the due date\n   - Add a tag/label strip at the top of the card if tags exist (small colored pills)\n   - Card click should open a slide-over detail panel (not a modal)\n\n2. **Column Component** (`components/board/column.tsx` or equivalent)\n   - Add a colored top-border accent per column status:\n       TO DO → blue, In Progress → yellow, Blocked → red, Done → green\n   - Add a \"+ Add card\" button at the TOP of the column (below the header), not just \n     the bottom\n   - Column header should have a subtle drag handle (⠿ icon, only visible on hover)\n   - Show a \"collapse column\" chevron button in the column header that reduces the \n     column to icon-only width\n\n3. **Board Header** (`components/board/board-header.tsx` or equivalent)\n   - Add a filter bar below the board title with:\n       • \"Assignee\" multi-select avatar filter\n       • \"Priority\" dropdown filter (All / High / Medium / Low)\n       • \"Due Date\" filter (Overdue / Due Soon / No Date)\n   - Add a \"Group by\" toggle (Status / Assignee / Priority)\n   - Add a board view switcher (Kanban icon | List icon) that persists to localStorage\n\n4. **Board Layout** (`app/boards/[id]/page.tsx` or equivalent)\n   - Columns should be horizontally scrollable with a fixed min-width of 280px each\n   - Add a keyboard shortcut `N` to open \"Add card\" in the focused/hovered column\n   - Maintain smooth auto-scroll when dragging a card near the edge of the viewport\n\n5. **Drag and Drop**\n   - Add a ghost/placeholder card that shows the drop position while dragging\n     (semi-transparent, dashed border)\n   - When a card is dragged over a different column, highlight that column's top-border\n     in a pulsing animation\n\n---\n\n### CONSTRAINTS\n- Do NOT change the data model or API calls — only UI/UX layer\n- Preserve all existing TypeScript types\n- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes only (no new CSS files)\n- Components must remain fully SSR-compatible (no `window` at module scope — use \n  `useEffect` for any browser APIs)\n- Keep all existing drag-and-drop library calls intact; only add visual enhancements\n\n---\n\n### DELIVERABLES\n1. Updated component files with inline comments explaining each AutoMaker-inspired change\n2. A brief summary of any new dependencies added (if any)\n3. Flag any places where you needed to deviate from AutoMaker's pattern due to our \n   data shape differences\n```\n\n---\n\n**A few tips for getting the best results from the agent:**\n\n- If your agent can browse GitHub, point it directly to the raw files: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AutoMaker-Org/automaker/main/apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/card.tsx`\n- If it can't, paste the relevant AutoMaker source files inline before the prompt above\n- Break it into two passes if needed: **Card + Column** first, **Board Header + Filters** second — the filter bar is the most complex piece and benefits from its own focused pass",
